\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Sebastian builds Block Ward, a pediatric emergency clinical simulator for RNs and medical students. He is a medical professional, not a developer. Tech stack: Vite + React (JavaScript, not TypeScript), Vercel serverless functions, Anthropic API via raw 
\f2\fs26 fetch()
\f1\fs24 . Repo 
\f2\fs26 kanudog/blockward
\f1\fs24  on GitHub, auto-deploys to Vercel on push to main. Local path 
\f2\fs26 /Users/openclaw/Documents/blockward
\f1\fs24  on a Mac Mini (username 
\f2\fs26 openclaw
\f1\fs24 ). Sebastian develops in Cursor with Claude Code running 
\f2\fs26 claude --dangerously-skip-permissions
\f1\fs24 . He runs 
\f2\fs26 vercel dev
\f1\fs24  (not 
\f2\fs26 npm run dev
\f1\fs24 ) because the app needs serverless functions for 
\f2\fs26 /api/generate
\f1\fs24 . Local dev URL is typically 
\f2\fs26 http://localhost:3000
\f1\fs24  from Vercel.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

