\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Things to know about Sonnet's orchestrator behavior\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f4\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 tied-correct
\f0\fs24  vs 
\f4\fs26 correct
\f0\fs24  is counterintuitive but consistent.
\f1\b0  
\f2\fs26 tied-correct
\f1\fs24  = must-have therapeutic for THIS pathology. 
\f2\fs26 correct
\f1\fs24  = supporting/preparatory (monitor, IV, stethoscope, blood cultures, CXR). Verified consistent across septic shock, dehydration, and anaphylaxis runs in this session.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Patient name diversity works.
\f1\b0  Sonnet draws from non-Western names without explicit prompting. Mateo Reyes, Amara Osei, Dilan \'d6zt\'fcrk, Farrukh Nazari, Tariq Osei across recent runs.\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Reassessment narratives land clinically.
\f1\b0  "She's crying louder now \'97 which, after what you just saw, is genuinely reassuring." Bedside voice landing.\
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 One creatinine edge case to expect occasionally.
\f1\b0  When Sonnet flags a lab as "approaching the upper limit" (e.g., creatinine 0.7 with ref 0.3-0.7), the dry-run script's strict numeric-inside-range check fires as a coherence violation. Clinically defensible, not a regression. Don't tighten the prompt for this.\
